Definition at line 23107 of file Messages.h.

Boolean::Enum contraryInstructionIndicator ( ) const
inlinenoexcept

Used to indicate when a contrary instruction for exercise or abandonment is being submitted: The exercise should not happen to an ITM position or it should happen to an ATM or OTM position, always using the values of tags 709-PosTransType and 712-PosMaintAction to determine which operation will take place.

Should not be submitted when false.
